{
  "texts": [
    "KEEPER focuses on efficiency by extracting only clinically relevant information for a specific phenotype, reducing data volume and expediting review.",
    "In practice, KEEPER uses structured data in a common format to extract pre-specified elements relevant to the disease during standard timewindows aligned with typical clinical reasoning steps.",
    "Configuring KEEPER for a specific outcome requires specifying the elementscaptured as sets of standard concepts in the OHDSI Standardized Vocabularies 7 --to extract per KEEPER category.",
    "For example, for acute appendicitis the 'Symptoms' category would specify concepts such as 'nausea', 'vomiting', and 'epigastric pain', and KEEPER would report if these concepts occurred in the 30 days prior to the case index date.",
    "The Supplementary Table 1 contains a full list of all KEEPER categories and corresponding time windows."
  ]
}